6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Continue and Tabnine share a solid foundation of core features including Autocomplete, Code Generation, Refactoring, Multi Language. Where Continue pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Debugging, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Tabnine uniquely offers Test Generation, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Continue holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Tabnine scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Continue offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $0, compared to Tabnine's starting price of $12/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Continue's free tier and Tabnine's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
